To install first go to https://github.com/ggrothendieck/sqldk
and click on commits at the right of the grey bar above the file tree.
If the top commit says Verified then it has been digitally signed.  This 
is not foolproof but it does give one layer of security.

Next issue this command from R to install sqldk and its dependencies:

  library(remotes)
  install_github("ggrothendieck/sqkdk")

To now access the package 

  library(sqldk)
  sqldk("select * from mtcars limit 3") # sample run

See the README file for more information.

